        {
          "name": "rate",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The playback rate for the item."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "itemTime",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The precise time at which to match playback of the item. To use the current itemâ€™s current time, specify "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coremedia/kcmtimeinvalid"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "hostClockTime",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The host time at which to synchronize playback. If you specify "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coremedia/kcmtimeinvalid"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", the rate and time are set together without any external synchronization. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method adjusts the current itemâ€™s timebase so that the time in "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "itemTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is in sync with the time in "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "hostClockTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Thus, if "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "hostClockTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " specifies a time in the past, the itemâ€™s timebase is adjusted to make it appear as if the item has been running at the specified rate since "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "itemTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". And if "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "hostClockTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " specifies a time in the future, playback is adjusted backward (if possible) so that the value in "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "itemTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " occurs at the precise moment the hostâ€™s clock reaches the value in "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "hostClockTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". If there is no content to play before the time specified by "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "itemTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", playback holds until the two times come into sync."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method does not ensure that media data is loaded before the timebase starts moving. However, if you specify a host time in the near future, that would give you some time to load the media data and prepare for playback."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "This method is not currently supported for HTTP Live Streaming or when "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1643482-automaticallywaitstominimizestal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". For clients linked against iOS 10.0 and later or macOS 10.12 and later, invoking this method when "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/avfoundation/avplayer/1643482-automaticallywaitstominimizestal"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " will raise an "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NSInvalidArgument"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " exception."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        }
      ]
    }
